restaurant.name: Barcade
restaurant.description: Went here for an engagement party. Wide selection of beer and wine and games to play.

restaurant.name: Miso Ramen
restaurant.description: Lenny really liked the pork ramen here. I had their chicken dumplings which weren't bad.

restaurant.name: Valenca
restaurant.description: They serve some food on hot plates, I had a tuna steak that you heat on the hot plate which was pretty good. Lenny had a 50$ steak. The prices seem high but portions are huge.

restaurant.name: Perkins Restaurant & Bakery
restaurant.description: A diner we stopped at because the other restaurants were closed. The food was fairly bland and not my favorite

restaurant.name: Cross Culture
restaurant.description: Indian food pretty flavorful for food you can find in Princeton. A staple for people who live here.

restaurant.name: Nomad Pizza
restaurant.description: Was pretty excited about the pizza here but the dough was a bit chewy and the sauce was lacking

restaurant.name: Boro Bean
restaurant.description: Had a wrap for brunch and it was pretty tasty. A pleasant quiet place to chill outside

restaurant.name: Peach Street Distillers
restaurant.description: The best bloody marys and really good old fashions. Their taco salad was spicy and flavorful. Phil the head distiller is very nice and gave us a free bottle of tequila

restaurant.name: Ale House
restaurant.description: The service was really slow when we were here, the food was okay and kind of cold by the time we got it.

restaurant.name: Main Street Bagels
restaurant.description: There's a reason why you should never eat a bagel outside of NYC. These bagels were very doughy.

restaurant.name: Pizzeria Limone
restaurant.description: Located inside Terminal A of the SLC airport, this pizza place really hits the spot while traveling. The pizzas are made fresh with a pizza oven.

restaurant.name: American Express Centurion Lounge Seattle
restaurant.description: Spent like 6 hrs here in 2023; the space was nice and hidden. Food was well seasoned and lots of veggie options. Lenny didnt like that there were no burger options for lunch. Their bloody mary was very good

restaurant.name: Rooftop Lounge
restaurant.description: Only had drinks here. They were good and had a nice view but def filled with a bunch of california moms eating brunch

restaurant.name: Anepalco Mexican Restaurant
restaurant.description: Pretty solid food and appetizers, the tuna tostada was disappointing though. But their Not Paella dish was really good.

restaurant.name: Gen Korean BBQ House
restaurant.description: A chain. Had to cook the kbbq ourselves but was pretty tasty. Loved the Cajun shrimp.

restaurant.name: Pizza Express
restaurant.description: A chain. Pizza was not bad and hit the spot after a long day of travel.

restaurant.name: Nando's
restaurant.description: A fast food chain. Chicken is very tasty and seasoned. The 2 level spice was not bad. Could do spice level 3 probably. The coleslaw and chips were pretty good. They have boneless and with bone options.

restaurant.name: Mielo
restaurant.description: Food was pretty good. They had a sea bass civeche and penne pasta with blue cheese. They had bread with hummus with olives and pickles for the complimentary appetizer. Desserts were not too sweet.

restaurant.name: Mercato Mayfair
restaurant.description: Lots of different food options in cart style. They had a gin bar and the cocktails there were all very good

restaurant.name: Negroni's
restaurant.description: Went here for drinks only. They had negroni sbagliatos with presecco!

restaurant.name: Bun House
restaurant.description: Everything here is delicious. They had many types of buns, loved the veggie buns!

restaurant.name: Ermei Sichuan Restaurant
restaurant.description: Was crowded but food is really good! The water boiled fish was super good with a numbing spice

restaurant.name: The Clarence
restaurant.description: Typical pub experience. Had a fish pie for the first time and it was not bad but really heavy.

restaurant.name: Hyde Park Winter Wonderland
restaurant.description: Seasonal location with a bunch of food for the holiday spirits. We had hot cocoa from a stand that was really chocolate-y.
